history.content:
The Data Science Discovery Program is excited to launch Discovery Exchange, an online hub for Berkeley students doing independent data science projects from Spring 2021 and beyond!
Come connect with other UC Berkeley undergraduate and graduate students in the data science and EE/CS community. Berkeley students from any background and level of exposure to data science and software development can participate. Students with no data science or software engineering background and curiosity for turning data into information are encouraged to check it out and jump in interdisciplinary projects.
Get a head start on your personal projects by joining our community and forming your own teams: www.discoveryexchange.org
Check out our Facebook page for more exciting events! facebook.com/discoveryexchange
If you have any questions, please reach out to ds-discovery@berkeley.edu. We are excited to welcome you to the Discovery Exchange community!
**This initiative is sponsored by the Division of Data Science. Relevant information can be found here: https://data.berkeley.edu/discovery-exchange
